    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, it feels like you're kind of dodging the actual point. like, even if there's automation and stuff, you can't deny that if people are getting checks that cover their basics, they're way less likely to go out and find work. aren't there specific studies or reports that show the safety net is actively discouraging people from entering the workforce?",
